mutant: m019_sync_tombstone_dropped
target: internal/ingest/live/events.go
failure-mode: |
  In convertSync, the KindSync tombstone row is dropped while verifier
  replacement rows are still emitted. Models a stream-fidelity bug where
  clients miss the authoritative sync boundary even though replacement records
  can make final repo state converge.
expected-detection: |
  Workstream 3 event-log equivalence compares simulator firehose #sync rows to
  post-append lifecycle hook observations keyed by UpstreamRelayCursor. The
  missing KindSync row should produce a "missing expected event" diagnostic in
  the default lifecycle oracle before final-state comparison can hide it.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

diff --git a/internal/ingest/live/events.go b/internal/ingest/live/events.go
index c9d264e..4ed61f9 100644
